  "preFix": {
    "title": "Wild mushroom and chestnut soup",
    "subtitle": "Deep, rich, and unmistakably autumnal",
    "excerpt": "A mix of fresh wild mushrooms and vacuum-packed chestnuts, cooked with shallots, thyme, and Madeira, then blended until thick and smooth. One of the most intensely flavoured autumn soups there is.",
    "sourceNotes": "Wild mushroom and chestnut soup draws on French and British autumn cooking traditions where mushrooms and chestnuts are treated as serious flavouring ingredients. No single canonical source.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Wild mushrooms and chestnuts have an affinity that makes this soup more than the sum of its parts. The mushrooms provide earthiness and depth; the chestnuts add a starchy sweetness and a creaminess that cream alone cannot replicate. Madeira, added after the mushrooms are cooked and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "reduced",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                  "attrs": {
                    "termId": "cmpry73dc0000lcv4leds36wf"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " before the stock goes in, gives the soup a warm, rounded quality that sets it apart from a standard mushroom soup. Use whatever wild or mixed mushrooms are available ,  chanterelles, girolles, oyster, or a supermarket mixed pack all work.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
