        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cook the mushrooms",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Melt {{unsalted-butter}} of butter in a large saucepan over a medium-low heat. Add the {{shallot}} shallots with a pinch of salt and cook for 6 minutes until soft. Add the {{garlic}} of garlic and {{thyme}} of thyme and cook for 1 minute.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{mushrooms-chestnut}} of sliced mushrooms. Turn the heat up to medium and cook for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally, until they have given off their liquid and the pan is nearly dry. This is where the flavour builds.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Add chestnuts and simmer",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{chestnuts}} of chopped chestnuts and stir for 1 minute. Pour in {{fortified-madeira}} of Madeira and let it reduce by half ,  about 2 minutes.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Pour in {{stock-chicken}} of hot stock. Simmer for 10 minutes.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Blend and finish",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Remove the thyme stalks. Blend in a jug blender until very smooth. Stir in {{double-cream}} of cream. Taste and season.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ladle into bowls. Add a swirl of cream and a few thyme leaves if desired.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "The step where the mushroom liquid evaporates is critical. Do not rush it or add stock too early. The mushrooms must concentrate before anything else goes in.",
                "cause": "The mushrooms were not cooked until properly dry and beginning to brown.",
                "symptom": "Soup tastes flat despite the ingredients"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Reduce the Madeira fully until less than half remains and the steam smells sweet rather than alcoholic. If too strong after blending, a squeeze of lemon juice helps.",
                "cause": "The Madeira was not reduced enough, leaving raw alcohol and over-sweet wine notes.",
                "symptom": "Madeira flavour is too pronounced"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Blend for at least 60 to 90 seconds in a jug blender. Pass through a fine-mesh sieve for a very smooth finish.",
                "cause": "Chestnuts can leave a slightly grainy texture if not blended long enough.",
                "symptom": "Texture is grainy"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Thin with hot stock or water a ladleful at a time after blending. The consistency should pour easily from a ladle.",
                "cause": "Chestnuts are starchy and thicken the soup considerably.",
                "symptom": "Too thick"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Wild mushrooms and chestnuts are autumn ingredients in both France and Britain: both appear in the forest at the same time of year and have been paired in cooking for centuries. In France, the combination appears in velouté de champignons and chestnut soups (soupe aux châtaignes) of the Périgord and Ardèche regions. In Britain, the soup became a restaurant and gastropub autumn staple in the 1990s. Vacuum-packed chestnuts, available year-round, make it a practical recipe beyond the October harvest.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
